crobatics of thought. Hans-Willi Weis, on the other hand, invites the reader on a sightseeing tour through intellectual Zeitgeist discourses. He connects the dots between the critique of outdated discourses, and a practice of attention which revitalizes thought and the discursive, and shows how we are individually capable of tackling the digital diffusion of attention and the compulsions of unlimited net activity through exercising methodical interruption.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aConduct of life. 0aIntellectuals. 0aSpiritual life. 4aDeutung. 4aDigitale Revolution. 4aDiskurs. 4aEthik. 4aIntellektuelle. 4aKultur. 4aKulturphilosophie. 4aLebenskunst. 4aMeditation. 4aPhilosophie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh  aArt of Living.  aCulture.  aDigital Revolution.  aDiscourse.  aEthics.  aIntellectuals.  aInterpretation.  aMeditation.  aPhilosophy of Culture.  aPhilosophy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2015z9783110438680oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070099208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839431757zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839431757423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839431757/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-070099-2  PP Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL